For fresh DRG analysis, DRG from lumbar segments L4, L5 and L6 were harvested and pooled. For DRG cultures, cells were collected after incubation with the drug and concentrated by centrifugation. RNA was extracted using TRIzol® Reagent (Invitrogen) according to the manufacturer’s instructions. Reverse transcription was performed using iScript™ Reverse Transcription Supermix (Bio-Rad) for RT-qPCR following the Bio-Rad supplied protocol. cDNA amplification was performed in triplicate, using SsoAdvanced™ Universal SYBR® Green Supermix (Bio-Rad) with the following primers;
Penk: forward 5’ TTCAGCAGATCGGAGGAGT 3’, reverse 5’ AGAAGCGAACGGAGGAGAC 3’;
Nav1.7 ex 7 forward 5’ TTTCCGGAAGGACCTTGAGC 3’, reverse CTGCCCTGAATCTGTGCTGA;
Nav1.7 ex 14 forward 5’ GAGCACCATCCAATGACGGA 3’, reverse 5’ TTCAGCTGCGAAGATCCCTG 3’;
Nfat5 ex 3-4 forward 5’ AGTCAGACAAGCGGTGGTGA 3’, reverse 5’ CAGACACTCCCTGCTTCAGAG 3’;
Nfat5 ex 6-7 forward 5’ TTGCAGACACCTTCTTCCCC 3’, reverse 5’ CTCTCCTTTCACTGAACAGCTA 3’;
Gapdh forward 5’ TGCGACTTCAACAGCAACTC 3’, reverse 5’ CTTGCTCAGTGTCCTTGCTG 3’. Amplification were conducted with the following program: 3 min at 95°C, 40 cycles of 60°C for 10 sec, 72°C for 10 sec, 95°C for 10 sec, and finally a melting curve for 10 min from 66°C to 100°C.
